🧩 Task Management System — FastAPI Project
A simple and lightweight task management system built using FastAPI .
This API allows you to create users, assign tasks, and manage task statuses with proper validation and error handling.

📦 Features
Create and view users
Add, view, and update tasks
Assign tasks to specific users
Validate input data (e.g., usernames, emails, due dates)
Use in-memory storage for quick development and testing
RESTful API design with proper status codes
🚀 Technologies Used
FastAPI – For building the API
Pydantic – For data validation
Uvicorn – ASGI server to run the app
🧪 API Endpoints Overview
POST
/users/
Register a new user
GET
/users/{user_id}
Get user details by ID
POST
/tasks/
Add a new task
GET
/tasks/{task_id}
Get task details by ID
PUT
/tasks/{task_id}
Update task status
GET
/users/{user_id}/tasks
Get all tasks assigned to a user

✅ Task Status Options
You can set task status to one of the following:

pending
in_progress
completed
🛠️ How to Run the project
1. Navigate to your project directory:
cd path/to/task_manager

python -m venv env
env\Scripts\activate      # Windows
source env/bin/activate   # Linux/Mac

2. Install the required packages:
pip install fastapi uvicorn pydantic
3. Run the FastAPI application:📋 Notes
All data is stored in memory (Python dictionaries), so it resets when the server restarts.
No external database or configuration needed – ideal for learning and testing.
Great for beginners to understand FastAPI fundamentals like routing, request/response models, and error handling.
💬 Need Help?
Agar kisi step par confusion ho ya error arahi ho, bas bata dein — main apki help karon ga 😊

